onso-admits-pain-of-adversity-has-re-lit-his-ambitions-1490258</link><title>Fernando Alonso Admits Pain of Adversity Has Re-Lit his Ambitions</title><description>Fernando Alonso said he had found facing adversity an experience that was painful, but necessary</description><a10:updated>2015-11-27T11:18:52+05:30</a10:updated></item><item><guid isPermaLink="false">1490299</guid><link>https://sports.ndtv.com/formula-1/lewis-hamilton-wants-to-end-triumphant-season-on-a-high-1490299</link><title>Lewis Hamilton Wants to End Triumphant Season on a High</title><description>Lewis Hamilton whose form and focus have drifted since he clinched his third drivers' title triumph at the United States Grand Prix in October, says he wants to thank his fans for their support with another triumph at the Yas Marina circuit.</description><a10:updated>2015-11-26T14:37:43+05:30</a10:updated></item><item><guid isPermaLink="false">1490344</guid><link>https://sports.ndtv.com/formula-1/bernie-ecclestone-has-no-doubts-monza-will-remain-on-formula-one-calendar-1490344</link><title>Bernie Ecclestone Has 'No Doubts' Monza Will Remain on Formula One Calendar</title><description>No circuit has hosted more Formula One racing than Monza, but officials at the track outside Milan have had trouble producing the estimated 25 million euros (USD 26.6 million) per year that Bernie Ecclestone seeks to keep the race in place after the current contract expires next year.</description><a10:updated>2015-11-25T20:42:47+05:30</a10:updated></item><item><guid isPermaLink="false">1490453</guid><link>https://sports.ndtv.com/formula-1/abu-dhabi-grand-prix-to-be-force-india-s-150th-formula-one-race-1490453</link><title>Abu Dhabi Grand Prix to be Force India's 150th Formula One Race</title><description>Force India finished fifth in the constructors' championship -- their best finish till date since coming into existence in 2008.</description><a10:updated>2015-11-23T22:22:58+05:30</a10:updated></item><item><guid isPermaLink="